The '''Alliance of Girls' Schools Australasia''' Ltd. was formed to promote the education of girls in single-sex girls' schools, and promote the image of, and support the development of, girls' schools in [[Australasia]].
The Alliance's first AGM was held in May 1996, where membership of the Alliance was extended to all girls' schools in [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]] whether independent, government or Catholic. The Alliance was incorporated 18 August 1997.<ref>[http://www.agsa.org.au/page/About/Our_History/ Our History], www.agsa.org.au</ref>
The alliance currently accepts membership from any school in Australia, New Zealand, Singapore, Hong Kong, the Philippines, and South Africa which is educating girls only.<ref>[http://www.agsa.org.au/page/About/ About us], www.agsa.org.au</ref>
It is affiliated with the [[Girls' Schools Association]] (GSA, UK) and the [[National Coalition of Girls' Schools]] (NCGS, US).<ref>[http://www.agsa.org.au/page/Members/Member_Benefits/ Member Benefits], www.agsa.org.au</ref>
