{{Infobox musical artist | name = Dilermando Reis | image = | caption = | image_size = | background = non_vocal_instrumentalist | birth_name = Dilermando dos Santos Reis | alias = | birth_place = [[Guaratinguetá]], [[São Paulo (state)|São Paulo]], [[Brazil]] | birth_date = {{Birth date|1916|9|22|mf=y}} | death_date = {{death date and age|1977|1|2|1916|9|22|mf=y}} |death_place =[[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Rio de Janeiro (state)|Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]] | instrument = [[Classical guitar]] | genre = [[Choro]], [[waltz]] | label = [[Columbia Records]], [[Continental Records]] | occupation = Musician, composer, arranger, music teacher | years_active = 1941–1977 | associated_acts = | website = }} '''Dilermando Reis''' (full name "Dilermando dos Santos Reis") (September 22, 1916 – January 2, 1977) was a Brazilian musician, composer, guitarist and music teacher.
He once had [[Juscelino Kubitschek]]'s (the former Brazilian president) daughter as a student. Other students included [[Bola Sete]], [[Nicanor Teixeira]], [[Darcy Vila Verde]] and many others.
He left 23 LPs as a soloist (often with unattributed accompaniment from Meira, or later Dino Sete Cordas) and seven accompanying the singer Francisco Petronio.<ref>[{{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p117815/biography|pure_url=yes}} Dilermando Reis biography] at [[allmusic]]</ref> [[David Russell (guitarist)|David Russell]] has performed his works on guitar. Raphael Rabello recorded an entire CD of his work.
